OL,6,FMrs McNamee said she advised that the
OL,7,Fparents of the girls should be
OL,8,Finformed and that she wanted to await
OL,9,Ftheir reactions before deciding the
OL,10,Fbest course of action to take as per
OL,11,Fthe Child Protection Policy.
OL,13,FThe principal said that after the
OL,14,Fparents of both pupils were spoken to,
OL,15,Fshe was told that whilst the parents
OL,16,Fwere concerned that Beckett's
OL,17,F"behaviour was perceived as being
OL,18,Finappropriate... both parties
OL,19,Funderstood at that time the context
OL,20,Fpossibly was a response to children
OL,21,Fbecoming upset".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
