OL,4,Cschool's welfare officer
OL,6,FShe added: "It was not presented as an
OL,7,Fallegation of being sexually
OL,8,Finappropriate at that time."
OL,10,FAn immediate meeting was then held
OL,11,Fwith Beckett and when asked about this
OL,12,Fby the Crown barrister, Mrs McNamee
OL,13,Fsaid she made the health and welfare
OL,14,Fofficer aware that "parents had raised
OL,15,Fconcerns about their children".
OL,17,FMrs McNamee said she told Beckett the
OL,18,Fnature of the concerns regarding the
OL,19,Fhugs which he denied doing.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
