OL,3,CPrincipal gives evidence at trial of
OL,4,Cschool's welfare officer
OL,6,FMrs McNamee told Mr MacCreanor that
OL,7,Fshe went over Beckett's role and job
OL,8,Fdescription at the meeting, which was
OL,9,Falso attended by an HR manager.
OL,11,FWhen asked if she discussed "the
OL,12,Fappropriateness of hugs" with him, Mrs
OL,13,FMcNamee said: "I did. I said to him
OL,14,Fthat in a school setting it wasn't
OL,15,Fappropriate and that, as per our
OL,16,Ftraining, if something does happen we
OL,17,Fare trained to report it to the
OL,18,Fdesignated teacher of child
OL,19,Fprotection."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
